Osborne Announces Cut in Northern Ireland Long-Haul Flight Tax

-- B y   T h o m a s   P e n n y
-- 
2011-09-27T13:34:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/osborne-announces-cut-in-northern-ireland-long-haul-flight-tax.html
U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer
 George Osborne  cut the tax on long-haul flights from airports in
Northern Ireland today to the same level as for short-haul
flights, the Treasury said in an e-mailed statement.  The cut will allow Continental Airlines Inc. flights from
Belfast International to Newark to continue to operate, the
Treasury said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Penny in Liverpool, England, at 
